The μτ product, which characterizes carrier drift length, is a fundamental property of a semiconductor material to predict the capability of extracting the charges deep inside the semiconductor. The μτ product can be determined by material types as well as defects, which is a parameter closely related to the charge carrier diffusion length LD with a relationship of LD=kBTμτ∕e1∕2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
